                <head>136. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>Although the United States never broke diplomatic relations with Uganda, the
                    Department of State closed the U.S. Embassy in Kampala on November 10, 1973, due
                    to security concerns and threats to U.S. citizens by high-ranking Ugandan
                    officials. <ref target="frus1969-76ve06#d240">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1969–1976, volume E–6, Documents
                        on Africa, 1973–1976, Documents 240</ref>–<ref target="frus1969-76ve06#d249"
                        >249</ref> describe the decision. The West German Embassy in Kampala
                    represented U.S. interests in Uganda.</p>
            </div>
